cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of segmenting objects in videos. The use of a neural network framework also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The inclusion of a memory module and the use of optical flow suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of temporal consistency and the focus on object segmentation suggest that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
